column5: at about 14H45 I decided to head out on the Sturgeon River ..3 minutes away and be back for supper ... I gassed up the boat and launched , and was on my spot at 15h05.....by 15h35 ..(66* surface temp 20FOW) I had caught 9 Walleye about the same size 36cm.. and a few Smallies followed and a then few Rock Bass .. then 2 more Walleye........ I kept fishing 'til I ran out of worms.  I pulled into the driveway at 17h05..I brought 4 of these home with me.   ........ heading back on Wednesday with Leeches and Minnows  I think the Falleye have arrived.   Randy
Walleyes, smallies and rock bass....no mishaps? Thanks for the report, Randy.
11 walleye? I guess I missed out.  Any slot size or all under?
Good fishing Randy! Enjoy the dinners.
No mishaps this time 'round Roy... It happens once in a while.   All identical.. within a CM or 2....   Just kept 4....  I went alone ....  Nipfisher was already back in Da-Bay.
Nice... one of these days your gonna have to take an old man out (me) for falleye!!
Nicely done, Randy!  Man oh man I wish I lived up there
Nice!!! Fishing like that can only be had up north!!! Lucky Bugger!!!!
Well done, about time someone gives Simon a run for his money!!!!
